title: Introduce a new way to manage outgoing calls state from ui.
message:
Introduce a new way to manage outgoing calls state from ui.
It introduce a new extra for start service intent that is optional.
If not used the service will run in background based on incoming mode settings. If used the service will consider we are in outgoing mode until the new broadcast intent are sent to unregister (or defer unregister).

title: Big commit to make csipsimple ui fancier for android 4.0 + base video stuff :
message:
Big commit to make csipsimple ui fancier for android 4.0 + base video stuff :
 * Added dependancy to ActionBarSherlock library
 * Start UI refactoring for ABS library.
 * Drop android 1.5 support which simplify many code and allow to use drawable folders a correct way
 * Remove divert because obsolete and complicated to maintain. Shall be only patches
 * Fixes some problems about pjsip strings and utf-8 inputs
 * Clean how swig glue is integrated by adding a clear interface to the way it get the jvm env
 * Add silk 12kHz (thx Juan Pablo)
 * Add libyuv dependancy of webRTC to toolchain process
 * Upgrade pjsip and add changes to amr in order to use the new sdp match function
 * Add webRTC capture and renderer glue for pjsip-2.0 which allow to do video stuff
 * Improve tablet screen user experience implementing a two pane mode with fragments use
 * Make cleaner the way string arrays are managed in translations
 * Call log refactoring to match android 4.0 ui
 * Call text refactoring to have a simplier and more efficient UI in tablet mode
Known issues :
 * Favorites tab does nothing
 * sip message ui broken
 * various ui glitch
